#   DIFF-005: `be diff:<file>` emits enormous (whole-file) context

`be diff:dog/INDEX.md` returns 110 lines for a 2-line edit — a single hunk
`@@ -1,106 +1,106 @@` spanning the ENTIRE file (2 added, 2 removed, *105
context*). For a tiny change in a large doc this is "enormous context for no
obvious reason." Likely DIFF-003's landed file-scoped full-file diff showing for
a single-file `diff:`; research whether that is intended/acceptable or should be
bounded. Evidence: [evidence]. Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  `be diff:dog/INDEX.md` (106-line file, +1 row edited) → 110 output lines, ONE
    hunk `@@ -1,106 +1,106 @@`, 2 `+` / 2 `-` / *105 context*. The whole file is
    emitted as context for a 2-line change. Full capture + repro: [evidence].
 -  DIFF-003 ("file-scoped diff: whole file, changes hilited") landed `eaa75793`, so
    a single-file `diff:<path>` plausibly renders the WHOLE file BY DESIGN. But the
    maintainer didn't expect/recognize it ("no idea why") — so either it's the
    intended file-scoped mode (and needs documenting / a bound for large files), or
    a context-sizing regression.

### Goals
 -  Determine: is the full-file context for `be diff:<file>` INTENDED (DIFF-003
    file-scoped) or a context-sizing bug? Cite the code path.
 -  Decide the right UX: if intended, bound it for large files and/or offer a
    git-style ~N-line-context mode, and DOCUMENT it so it stops surprising; if a
    bug, fix the context window.

### Constraints
 -  Don't regress DIFF-003's deliberate full-file-with-highlight view where that is
    wanted (e.g. the pager); the concern is the plain `be diff:<file>` text output.
 -  Behaviour change to diff context gates for review; add a test pinning the chosen
    context size for a small-edit-in-large-file case.

##  WIP

### Design decisions (scan done 2026-06-16 — INTENDED, not a bug)
 -  PREMISE CORRECTED (bare-`be diff` re-investigation): the bare aggregate
    `be diff:` is ALREADY bounded — every hunk is 3-line context
    (`GRAFDiffWtTree`→`GRAFDiffWtFile(full=NO)`→`WEAVEEmitDiff`). The whole-file
    inflation is ONLY the single-file `diff:<file>` projector (`full=YES`). So this
    ticket stays a single-file-projector concern; do NOT add bare-diff handling, and
    drop the "bare diff is whole-file" framing.
 -  The re-investigation surfaced two ADJACENT defects, now their own tickets:
    [DIFF-006] (cosmetic: per-hunk `--- a/`/`+++ b/` repeated, not coalesced per
    file — the "62 headers vs 17 files" artifact, `dog/HUNK.c:1242`) and [DIFF-007]
    (REAL bug: `diff:<largefile>` silently EMPTY — `WEAVEEmitFull`'s 65536-token
    `outtoks` carve overflows on big files, NOROOM swallowed; `WEAVE.c:1030/1099`).
    Note: option-a here (bound large files → `WEAVEEmitDiff`) would INCIDENTALLY mask
    DIFF-007, a strong extra argument for it.
 -  VERDICT: the whole-file context is DELIBERATE DIFF-003 design, hard-wired
    `full=YES` for single-file `diff:` shapes. Decision site `GRAFDiff2Layer`
    (`graf/DIFFREF.c:163`): `if (full) WEAVEEmitFull` (no windowing, `WEAVE.c:1015`)
    else `WEAVEEmitDiff` (3-line `WEAVE_CTX_LINES`, `WEAVE.c:802/850`). Intent
    documented verbatim at `DIFFREF.c:108-117` + `GRAF.h:315-317`. No context knob.
 -  Only the single-file `diff:<file>` projector is unbounded (`GRAF.exe.c:512`
    wt-vs-base, `:502` ref, `:438` range). Tree-scope (`DIFFREF.c:377`) and the
    `weave` verb (`GRAF.exe.c:567`) ALREADY use the bounded 3-line path — so the
    machinery for git-style context exists.
 -  UX options (maintainer call — see Outcome): (a) BOUND LARGE FILES — at
    `DIFFREF.c:163`, when `full && line_count > N` (~200) demote to `WEAVEEmitDiff`;
    small files keep the full read (one-site, no API churn — worker's preferred).
    (b) SPLIT pager-vs-text — tty/`HUNKMode` → full, non-tty → 3-line (touches the 3
    dispatch sites). (c) KEEP + DOCUMENT only (it self-documents already).

